{"type":"message","id":"bae34cd4","parentId":"c8a5038f","timestamp":"2026-04-11T13:30:53.521Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a heartbeat poll. The user gave me a task earlier to implement multi-model routing - Phase 1 and Phase 1.5. I was in the middle of editing the proxy/index.js file when the heartbeat came.\n\nLet me check if there's anything that needs attention related to the current task:\n\n1. Phase 1 was completed - configs created, validated\n2. Phase 1.5 - I was editing proxy/index.js to add routing logic\n\nI made the first edit adding the routing config loading and functions. Then I tried to edit the message handler but made a mistake with a \"replace: false\" property. Then I successfully made a second edit that added the routing logic to the message handler.\n\nHowever, I notice there's a problem - in the new code I added, I'm calling classify() twice:\n1. Once in my new routing decision logic\n2. Once in the original code that still exists after my edit\n\nThis would cause issues. Let me check the current state of the file and see if there's anything that needs immediate attention.\n\nActually, this is a heartbeat poll. The task is still in progress but I'm not blocked - I can continue working on it. There's no emergency that requires attention right now.\n\nI should respond with HEARTBEAT_OK since nothing critical needs immediate attention - the work is in progress","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":37834,"output":278,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38112,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775914248150,"responseId":"chatcmpl-9dde3e46-95be-42d2-a69e-baec4a1937a0"}}
